\v 2 \w A|strong="G1722"\w* long \w time|strong="G1722"\w* ago, \w God|strong="G3588"\w* \w promised|strong="G4279"\w* \w to|strong="G1722"\w* \w do|strong="G1223"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w*. \w He|strong="G3739"\w* got \w some|strong="G3739"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w his|strong="G1223"\w* \w men|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G1722"\w* tell \w people|strong="G3588"\w* \w about|strong="G1722"\w* \w it|strong="G1223"\w*, \w and|strong="G4396"\w* \w they|strong="G3588"\w* wrote \w about|strong="G1722"\w* \w it|strong="G1223"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w God|strong="G3588"\w*’s \w book|strong="G3588"\w*.  
\v 3-4 That good news is about our leader Jesus Christ. He was born into David’s family. David was the big boss of the Jewish nation a long time ago. Jesus was born as a human being into David’s family, but really, Jesus is God’s own son. God showed us in a powerful way that Jesus is his son. He did it like this. People killed Jesus, but God used his Holy Spirit to make him alive again.   
\p
